---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageShell from "../../components/PageShell.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Equal Opportunities Policy | Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC"
  description="Equal Opportunities Policy for Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC."
>
  <PageShell>
    <section class="py-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">

        <a
          href="/policies"
          class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-300 hover:text-blue-200"
        >
          ← Back to Policies
        </a>

        <div class="mt-10">
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-blue-300">
            Club Policies
          </p>

          <h1 class="text-5xl font-light tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">
            Equal Opportunities Policy
          </h1>

          <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-300">

            <p>
              Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC is committed to providing an inclusive,
              welcoming and positive environment for all players, volunteers,
              coaches, officials and supporters.
            </p>

            <p>
              The club believes that everyone should have the opportunity to
              participate in football regardless of age, disability, gender,
              race, religion, ethnic background, sexual orientation or
              socio-economic background.
            </p>

            <p>
              WWFC aims to promote fairness, respect and equal opportunity
              throughout all club activities and expects all members to support
              these values both on and off the pitch.
            </p>

            <p>
              The club will not tolerate discrimination, bullying, harassment
              or abusive behaviour in any form and will investigate concerns
              appropriately in line with FA guidance and safeguarding procedures.
            </p>

            <p>
              Further updates and detailed policy guidance will be published as
              the club continues to develop its governance framework.
            </p>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>
  </PageShell>
</Layout>